TWO brothers Ishmael Mopai (28)
and his sibling Michael Mopai (30) appeared in the Lulekani  Magistrate's Court on charge of murder, for
allegedly beheading their sister. The brothers were arrested
in February, in connection to an alleged ritual murder of their sister Irene
Mopai (40). The case was postponed to
25 June, and they were reminded  in
custody  to allow further police  investigations. Police spokesperson
Constable Maphure Manamela said the deceased's beheaded body was found in their
home by a relative in Matiko Xikaya village outside Phalaborwa. He said following the
arrest, the sisterthe deceased's head was recovered in the bushes. 